Docker Volumes
=============

	Ø Docker volume is nothing but it’s a directory 
	Ø You are going to declaring a volume as a directory 
	Ø Volume is a directory inside a container
	Ø First declare a directory as a volume
	Ø Volume will be created in one container
	Ø It is better or good approach to create a volume along with ur container
	Ø Once container got created its difficult to attach the volume to the container
	Ø You can share one volume with n.no of containers
	Ø Volume will not be included when you are going to update ur docker image 
	Ø Becz volume is going to creating out side of the file system 


Types of volumes
==============

Anonymous volumes:- there is no meaningful name to the volumes